2024 was a year that knocked me down so hard, seeing so many recaps of 2024 i thought of making one but damn I don’t  want to relive it. Lost myself, lost my job, lost so many things I can’t even put into words. 
But here I am, picking myself up, not running from my problems anymore. Coming back home, being around  my parents and a few friends, has given me the strength to stand tall again. I’ve learned my lessons the hard way, but still believing in “for all that falls apart, something beautiful is coming together. 
2025, as Rocky Randhava would have said “I am a fragileee, please handle with care”.

For the past six months, I’ve been navigating a tough battle with stomach colitis. It’s brought on intense inflammation, relentless bloating, and a level of discomfort I wouldn’t wish on anyone. Despite staying consistent with my workouts, my body started holding onto water and weight like never before. It’s been frustrating, to say the least feeling like all the effort wasn’t showing the results it should.
But here’s the thing: I’ve been here before. I’ve faced setbacks, and I’ve come back stronger each time. This isn’t the end of my story, it’s just another chapter. And I know, deep down, I’ve got what it takes to overcome this. I’ve done it once. I’ll do it again.
